summary:
Ever since the beginning of my academic education, my goal has been to become a teacher who can contribute to a change in attitudes towards social norms and in teachers' behaviours that seem anachronistic. 

In my teaching, I have succeeded in developing strong bonds of trust, both between teacher and student and between teacher and parents. 

I have experience working with children of migrants, bilingual and multilingual pupils, children that experienced family instabilities, and children with mental, motor and learning difficulties.
